# Legendary Hunts — Cursor rules (root pointer)

Canonical project rules live under **`.cursor/rules/`**, especially:

- `.cursor/rules/alignment.mdc` — architecture, encounter model, tier rules, integration boundaries
- `.cursor/rules/phase-completion.mdc` — handoff template for completed phases

Product requirements: **`.cursor/rules/PRD.md`**

When generating code, follow alignment first; the PRD describes product vision and Network+ scope. If the PRD conflicts with alignment on **technical** matters (core vocabulary, encounter variability, Slack vs core boundaries), **alignment wins**.
